rn auto engines are operable under high mechanical, thermal load conditions and therefore require   lubricants  of superior quality.   In order to improve the operational efficiency of engine, lubricant manufacturers profuse the oil with series of multi-task additives. For instance,  Extreme Pressure additives significantly reduce the wear of working parts, reduce  varnish deposits within different units of  engine, prevent, etc. Modern oils contain over 10   different additives executing different tasks. Although there are great abundance of  data regarding properties of oil,  it is necessary for average consumer  to pay attention to 2 major characteristics:  quality level ( compatibility with car engine) and viscosity level ( compatibility with given season and environment (climate)). All the  answers are described on   grading systems of various international organizations.   </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 9.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\"> </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 9.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; mso-farea