B1 1.0pt; border-right: solid #A2A9B1 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A2A9B1 .75pt; mso-border-left-alt: solid #A2A9B1 .75pt; mso-border-alt: solid #A2A9B1 .75pt; padding: 2.4pt 4.8pt 2.4pt 4.8pt;\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\">Mineral oils ( containing  Extreme Pressure additives with high effectiveness and multifunctional performance ) including universal oils </span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid #A2A9B1 1.0pt; border-right: solid #A2A9B1 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt: solid #A2A9B1 .75pt; mso-border-left-alt: solid #A2A9B1 .75pt; mso-border-alt: solid #A2A9B1 .75pt; padding: 2.4pt 4.8pt 2.4pt 4.8pt;\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\">  Hypoid gears operating with high shock load under contact stress  up to 3000 mPA and  up to 150°</span><span lang=\"RU\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;\">С</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\">  oil  </span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 3.6pt 0cm 0.0001pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.5pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\"> </span></span></h3>\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 3.6pt 0cm 0.0001pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.5pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\">Example of  transmission oil designation</span></span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 6pt 0cm; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span lang=\"RU\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;\">ТМ</span></b><b><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\">-5-9</span></b><b><sub><span lang=\"RU\" style=\"font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;\">З</span></sub></b></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 6pt 0cm; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span lang=\"RU\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;\">ТМ</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\"> — transmission oil;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 6pt 0cm; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\">5</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\"> —  oil with extreme pressure(high effectiveness)  and other multifunctional additives ;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 6pt 0cm; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\">9</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\"> — viscosity grade;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 6pt 0cm; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span lang=\"RU\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;\">З</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\"> — oil contains thickening agents .</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<table style=\"width: 1132px;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 503px;\">\r\n<h1 style=\"margin-top: 0cm; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: \'Verdana\',\'sans-serif\'; color: red; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\">ATF - III – IV – V Charateristic</span></h1>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 12.75pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\">Automatic Transmission Fluids (ATF)  along with brake fluids and hydraulic fluids of steering systems, are considered the most specific products of auto-chemistry.  It is possible to  start engine  and even run the car  for some time, after  completely discharging the oil. But same cannot be said about Automatic Transmission Fluids.  By completely discharging the fluid, you immediately  turn your gear box into useless piece of sophisticated mechanism.  Today,   auto transmission fluids  shall meet high standards for viscosity,   antifriction, anti-oxidation, anti-wear and extreme pressure (anti-scuff)  as compared to other lubricants and oils. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"RU\" style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; color: #181818;\"><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">ATF has wide range of functions, since</span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">  </span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">automatic gear box is rather complex mechanism comprised of series of units – torque converter, pinion drive,</span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">  </span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">complex control system, etc. ATF performs multi-tasks: lubricates, cools,</span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">  </span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">protects from rust and corrosion,</span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">  </span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">provides torsion torque and friction clutch.</span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">   </span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Average oil temperature inside transmission casing may is between 80-90 C, in a hot weather, in stop-and go city driving conditions it can rise up to 150 C.</span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">    </span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Structure of</span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">  </span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">automatic transmission is rather sophisticated, thus,</span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">  </span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">when</span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">  </span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">engine discharge more power than required for</span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">  </span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">managing road resistance, surplus is spent on internal friction of oil, which eventually gets warmer.</span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">  </span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">High speed circulation of fluid inside torque converter and high temperature leads to intensive airing which results in foaming and create favourable conditions for oxidation and corrosion of metals. </span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">Diversity of materials involved in friction ( steel,</span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">  </span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">yellow metal, cermet, friction</span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">  </span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">gaskets, elastomers)</span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">  </span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">makes it difficult to pick proper anti-friction additives and generate electrochemical steam</span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">  </span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">that can initiate corrosive wear</span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">  </span><span style=\"color: black; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">in presence of air and water.</span>.</span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 420px;\">   <img src=\"images/banners/ATFIII.jpg\" alt=\"\" />         </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-indent: 14.2pt;\"> </p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 12.75pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\">Under those conditions, fluid must preserve not only its performance properties (qualities), but also provide high efficiency of transmission. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 12.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\">General Specifications</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 12.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\">Historically,  General Motors and Ford   hold have been main players in defining the standards for automatic transmission fluids (See Table 1). European car and lubrication/ transmission oil  manufacturers do not have specifications of their own, therefore adhere to oil lists  approved by them.  The same can be said about Japanese car manufacturers.  Early automatic transmissions run simple motor oil, thereby  making it necessary to change the oil regularly and transmission was of inferior quality.  </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 12.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\">General Motors introduced the first  automatic transmission fluid  ATF –A  service-fill specification in 1949, that had been applied for all  automatic gear boxes at that time.   Specification was revised to Type A Suffix A (ATF TASA) in 1957.  Automatic Transmission Fluids produced during those years  contained whale oil as a friction modifier.  Due to rising market demand   and  commercial whale hunting ban, manufacturers developed  mineral and years later, synthetic automatic transmission fluids.      General Motors  introduced its new specifications Dexron B in 1967, later Dexron II, Dexron III and Dexron IV. Specifications Dexron III and Dexron IV  are developed  with  main focus  on Torque Flite transmission. This specification required improved oxidation and corrosion control in GM electronic automatics. General Motors also developed and introduced specification  Allison C-4 ( Allison – is  unit of General Motors specialized in transmission production)  defining requirements for ATF used in trucks and off-road vehicles    operating under severe  conditions.  For a long time, Ford did not have its own ATF specifications and used  ATF-A specification of General Motors. But  company eventually developed and released  specification, M2C33-A/B in 1959.  Later,  ESW-M2C33-F (ATF-F) had become  widely applied specification. Ford released  specification of M2C33-D in 1961, with main focus on  meeting  modern requirements for frictional properties of oils, followed  by Mercon that was introduced in 80s.  ATFs  complying with the requirement of Mercon, are almost equivalent to those complying with specifications of Dexron II and Dexron III.   Main  difference between specifications of General  Motors and Ford – are  requirements for frictional properties of fluids  (General Motor specifications emphasize on softness of shift, when Ford mainly focus on speed of tranmission) General ATF features and qualities are given in Table 2. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 12.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><a name=\"tab1\"></a><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; f