dowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; padding: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center; line-height: 15.0pt;\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Verdana\',\'sans-serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\"> Absence of visible rust</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"border: solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-top: none; mso-border-top-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; padding: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 15.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Verdana\',\'sans-serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\">ASTM test method D-2882 (for indicating wear characteristics)   (80 0C, 6,9 mP</span><span lang=\"RU\" style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Verdana\',\'sans-serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;\">а</span><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Verdana\',\'sans-serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\">): mass loss, mg, above </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 15.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Verdana\',\'sans-serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\"> </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 15.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Verdana\',\'sans-serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\"> </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 18.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: RU;\">Gear Oil   </span></b><b><span lang=\"RU\" style=\"font-size: 18.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: RU;\">80w90</span></b></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-right: solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-left-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; padding: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"RU\" style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; line-height: 115%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;\"> </span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-right: solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-left-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; padding: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\"> </td>\r\n<td style=\"border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-right: solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-left-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; padding: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\"> </td>\r\n<td style=\"border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-right: solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-left-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; padding: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\"> </td>\r\n<td style=\"border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: solid windowtext 1.0pt; border-right: solid windowtext 1.0pt; mso-border-top-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-left-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; padding: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\"> </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;\"> </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 6pt 0cm; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: RU;\">Gear oil  </span></b><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: RU;\">80W90 is  high quality lubrication intended for gear boxes, transfer cases and differentials of    automobile, truck and other vehicles. Featuring high viscosity, it provides good protection for gears  and usually is associated with  a strong sulfur smell. High viscosity ensures transfer of lubrication  throughout the gear train.  This is necessary since the devices needing this heavy oil do not have pumps for transferring the oil, with only a portion of the lowermost gears are bathed in an oil sump.  This heavy oil can create viscous drag  leading to inefficiencies  in vehicle operation. Some modern  automatic transaxles  do not use  a heavy oil at all, but lubricate with low viscosity hyraulic fluid,  which is available at pressure within automatic transmission.  </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 6pt 0cm; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: RU;\">Most lubricants for mechanical transmissions and differentials contain Extreme Pressure  and anti-wear additives  to cope with  sliding action of hypoid bevel gears. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; text-align: center; line-height: normal; background: #F8F9FA;\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: RU;\"> </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 16.8pt; background: #F8F9FA;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9.5pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: RU;\">Gear oils  are  also being added to the final reduction gears in a scooter.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; background: #F8F9FA;\"><span style=\"font-size: 9.5pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: RU;\">Extreme Pressure additives which contain phosporus-sulfur compounds cause corrosion of yellow metal i.e  copper or brass used in bushings and synchronizers.  Category GL-1  gear oils do not contain   any EP additives, therefore  finds use in applications made of yellow metals.  GL-5 is not necessarily backward-compatible in synchro-mesh  transmission  which are designed for a GL-4 oil: GL-5 has a lower friction cooeficency  due to higher concentration of EP additives  over GL4 and therefore synchros cannot engage as effectively. Also,  transmissions which explicitly  call for GL-4 oil may have been designed  around  this lower concentration of EP additives and thus may contain yellow metal parts which GL-5 will corrode. </span></p>',
